cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the design of a scalable authentication infrastructure for the Internet, which involves security and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
